> Hiya All,
> 
> First off, I need to thank Joe over at Busted VW for his information 
> concerning the Slider Hinge Link Assembly.
> 
> But now another question has popped up.  In talking to a boneyard mechanic 
> about removing the sliding door hinge link assembly, he told me 
> this.......................
> 
> "Don't follow the procedure in Bentley (remove door, remove body track cover, 
> remove old and install new hinge) for replacing the hinge link.  Taking off 
> the body track cover (the screws will be all rusted, etc, etc,) will just 
> result in a ruined track cover.  And then I'll be left with hours of 
> adjusting the door.  Instead, just jack up the slider slightly, undo the 
> hinge bolts from the inside and slip the hinge link assembly back down the 
> track and (manuevering it around a bit) take it out of the track at the track 
> slot."
> 
> Whaddyathink guys?  This is my first time at this particular job.  I don't 
> want to mess this up.
> 
> Mike   
